# üêû bug report

### Affected Package

I believe the issue is caused by package @angular/router.

### Is this a regression?

Not sure if that ever worked.

### Description

When `routerLink` is used as an input of a custom component, e.g.:

```
@Component({
  selector: 'app-link-wrapper',
  template: `
    <a [routerLink]="routerLink"><ng-content></ng-content></a>
  `,
})
export class LinkWrapperComponent {
  @Input() routerLink: string;
}
```

And that the route navigating to has an async guard:

```
@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root',
})
export class TestGuard implements CanActivate {
  canActivate(
    route: ActivatedRouteSnapshot,
    state: RouterStateSnapshot,
  ) {
    return Rx.of(undefined).pipe(
      delay(100),
      map(() => true),
    );
  }
}
```

And that the Router `urlUpdateStrategy` is set to `eager`

Then the navigation is broken, as if the guard was unsubscribed to before emitting its value.

If any of the above conditions is not true, then the navigation works as expected, i.e.:
- If the `routerLink` input of `LinkWrapperComponent` is renamed to `myRouterLink`
- If the route guard returns synchronously
- If `urlUpdateStrategy` is not set to `eager`

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

Minimal repro in https://github.com/laurentgoudet/angular-nester-routerLink-eager-urlUpdateStrategy-bug. All the code is in https://github.com/laurentgoudet/angular-nester-routerLink-eager-urlUpdateStrategy-bug/blob/master/src/app/app-routing.module.ts.

